{"parse":{"title":"Guidance Patrol","pageid":51390526,"revid":854369365,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For 2012 film, see <a href=\"/wiki/Guidance_Patrol%3F!\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Guidance Patrol?!\">Guidance Patrol?!</a></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gasht_Ershad.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Gasht_Ershad.JPG/220px-Gasht_Ershad.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"209\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Gasht_Ershad.JPG/330px-Gasht_Ershad.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Gasht_Ershad.JPG/440px-Gasht_Ershad.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"554\" data-file-height=\"527\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gasht_Ershad.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A Guidance Patrol <a href=\"/wiki/Mitsubishi_Delica\" title=\"Mitsubishi Delica\">Delica van</a> parked in front of <a href=\"/wiki/Mellat_Park\" title=\"Mellat Park\">Mellat Park</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Tehran\" title=\"Tehran\">Tehran</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Guidance Patrol</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Persian_language\" title=\"Persian language\">Persian</a>: <span lang=\"fa\" dir=\"rtl\">\u06af\u0634\u062a \u0627\u0631\u0634\u0627\u062f</span>&#8206;, <i>ga\u0161t-e er\u0161\u0101d</i>; also known as <b>morality police</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>) is a kind of <a href=\"/wiki/Vice_squad\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vice squad\">vice squad</a> in the <a href=\"/wiki/Law_Enforcement_Force_of_Islamic_Republic_of_Iran\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Law Enforcement Force of Islamic Republic of Iran\">Law Enforcement Force of Islamic Republic of Iran</a>, established in 2005<sup id=\"cite_ref-a0_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> with the task to arrest mostly women (but also some men)<sup id=\"cite_ref-a2_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a2-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> who deem improperly dressed according to the <a href=\"/wiki/Hijab_by_country#Iran\" title=\"Hijab by country\">dress code</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Consistency\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Consistency</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Controversy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Controversy</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Plan_Lose\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Plan Lose</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Consistency\">Consistency</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Guidance_Patrol&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Consistency\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The patrols usually consist of a <a href=\"/wiki/Van\" title=\"Van\">van</a> with male crew accompanied by <i><a href=\"/wiki/Chador\" title=\"Chador\">chador</a></i>-clad females that stand at busy public places e.g. shopping centers, squares and subway stations to pry, intercept and detain <i>bad-<a href=\"/wiki/Hijab\" title=\"Hijab\">hijabs</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-a0_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-a4_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a4-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> They are driven to a correctional facility or police station, lectured on how to dress and almost always released on the same day<sup id=\"cite_ref-a4_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a4-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> after their fathers, husbands or brothers go to the station to get them released.<sup id=\"cite_ref-a0_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2013's <a href=\"/wiki/Mother%27s_Day#Iran\" title=\"Mother&#39;s Day\">Iranian Mother's Day</a>, the patrols rewarded flowers to women for wearing <i><a href=\"/wiki/Chador\" title=\"Chador\">chador</a></i> (the preferred hijab style).<sup id=\"cite_ref-a4_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a4-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Controversy\">Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Guidance_Patrol&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>A matter of controversy in Iran, some officials and authorities state that based on their interpretation of Iranian police as an <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_religious_police\" title=\"Islamic religious police\">Islamic religious police</a>, the Guidance Patrols serve to fulfill the requisites <i><a href=\"/wiki/Enjoining_good_and_forbidding_wrong\" title=\"Enjoining good and forbidding wrong\">enjoining what is right and forbidding what is wrong</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-a1_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a1-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and are demanded by the people.<sup id=\"cite_ref-a3_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a3-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Others oppose their existence on the grounds that the police should respect <a href=\"/wiki/Civil_liberties\" title=\"Civil liberties\">citizens' freedom</a> and dignity,<sup id=\"cite_ref-a2_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a2-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and enforce the law, not <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sharia\" title=\"Sharia\">sharia</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> They have also been criticized for being un-Islamic,<sup id=\"cite_ref-a3_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a3-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> most importantly because performing the requisites is <i><a href=\"/wiki/Haraam\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Haraam\">haraam</a></i> (forbidden) when it leads to sedition.<sup id=\"cite_ref-a1_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a1-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> It is also argued that the notion is a mutual obligation (including remonstrating officials by the people as well) limited to one side.<sup id=\"cite_ref-a1_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-a1-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Plan_Lose\">Plan Lose</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Guidance_Patrol&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Plan Lose\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Majlis_Research_Center\" title=\"Majlis Research Center\">Research Center of Iranian Parliament</a> announced in 2015 that <b>Guidance Patrol</b> plan reached a lose reason of which was disregarding to the people's wishes and demands calling its results \"negative\" and stayed against its totalities.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On 27 December 2017, Brig. Gen. Hossein Rahimi, head of Greater <b>Tehran police</b>, said, \u201cAccording to the commander of the <b>NAJA</b> - <a href=\"/wiki/Law_Enforcement_Force_of_the_Islamic_Republic_of_Iran\" title=\"Law Enforcement Force of the Islamic Republic of Iran\">Law Enforcement Force of the Islamic Republic of Iran</a>, those who do not observe Islamic values and have negligence in this area will no longer be taken to detention centers, a legal case will not be made for them and we will not send them to court; rather, education classes to reform their behavior will be offered.\u201d <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Guidance_Patrol&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-36101150\">Who are Islamic 'morality police'?</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-a0-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-a0_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a0_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a0_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Erdbrink, Thomas (7 May 2014). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/08/world/middleeast/when-freedom-is-the-right-to-stay-under-wraps.html\">\"When Freedom Is the Right to Stay Under Wraps\"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=When+Freedom+Is+the+Right+to+Stay+Under+Wraps&amp;rft.date=2014-05-07&amp;rft.aulast=Erdbrink&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2014%2F05%2F08%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fwhen-freedom-is-the-right-to-stay-under-wraps.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-a2-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-a2_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a2_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Sharafedin, Bozorgmehr (20 April 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-rights-rouhani-idUSKCN0XH0WH\">\"Rouhani clashes with Iranian police over undercover hijab agents\"</a>. <i>Reuters</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Reuters&amp;rft.atitle=Rouhani+clashes+with+Iranian+police+over+undercover+hijab+agents&amp;rft.date=2016-04-20&amp;rft.aulast=Sharafedin&amp;rft.aufirst=Bozorgmehr&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-iran-rights-rouhani-idUSKCN0XH0WH&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-a4-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-a4_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a4_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a4_4-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.economist.com/blogs/pomegranate/2013/05/iran\">\"Iran: Fashion police\"</a>. <i>Economist</i>. 5 May 2013<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Economist&amp;rft.atitle=Iran%3A+Fashion+police&amp;rft.date=2013-05-05&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fblogs%2Fpomegranate%2F2013%2F05%2Firan&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-a1-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-a1_5-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a1_5-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a1_5-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Adib, Muhammad Jawad (26 September 2013). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2013/09/iran-police-morals-rise-confrontations.html\">\"Iran's 'Guidance Patrols' Stir Controversy\"</a>. <i>Al-Monitor</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Al-Monitor&amp;rft.atitle=Iran%E2%80%99s+%27Guidance+Patrols%27+Stir+Controversy&amp;rft.date=2013-09-26&amp;rft.aulast=Adib&amp;rft.aufirst=Muhammad+Jawad&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Fpulse%2Foriginals%2F2013%2F09%2Firan-police-morals-rise-confrontations.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-a3-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-a3_6-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-a3_6-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Faghihi, Rohollah (6 May 2016). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/iran-tehran-morality-police-1509213622/\">\"Morality police go undercover to keep Tehran under cover\"</a>. <i>Middle East Eye</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Middle+East+Eye&amp;rft.atitle=Morality+police+go+undercover+to+keep+Tehran+under+cover&amp;rft.date=2016-05-06&amp;rft.aulast=Faghihi&amp;rft.aufirst=Rohollah&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fnews%2Firan-tehran-morality-police-1509213622%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Karami, Arash (27 April 2015). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/en/originals/2015/04/iran-police-enforce-islam-rouhani.html\">\"Rouhani: Police should not enforce Islam\"</a>. <i>Al-Monitor</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Al-Monitor&amp;rft.atitle=Rouhani%3A+Police+should+not+enforce+Islam&amp;rft.date=2015-04-27&amp;rft.aulast=Karami&amp;rft.aufirst=Arash&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Fpulse%2Fen%2Foriginals%2F2015%2F04%2Firan-police-enforce-islam-rouhani.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGuidance+Patrol\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span